The paper deals with algorithms for computing persistent homology, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and topological data analysis (cs.DS). The paper also discusses theoretical complexity analysis and experimental results, which are common in algorithms research (cs.DM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper mentions the Gudhi library, which is a software tool for topological data analysis and computational topology (cs.SY).
